fIcy
------------------------------------------
fIcy is a small icecast/shoutcast stream grabber suite for use under shell
environment. Its goal is to automatically rip a stream into user customisable
files. It will work with ICY compatible streams, allowing you to either to
save the stream to disk or to pipe the output to a media player, or even both.
fIcy, among other uses, is ideal for batch/unattended recording of radio
programs and stream debugging.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libgcc1-6.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-6.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.thregr.org/~wavexx/software/fIcy/

Canonical download:
  http://www.thregr.org/~wavexx/software/fIcy/releases/fIcy-1.0.21.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack fIcy-1.0.21-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./fIcy-1.0.21-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/fIcy-1.0.21-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/fIcy-1.0.21-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(fIcy)
  /usr/bin/fIcy.exe
  /usr/bin/fPls.exe
  /usr/bin/fResync.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/fIcy.README
  /usr/share/doc/fIcy/COPYING.txt
  /usr/share/doc/fIcy/FAQ.rst
  /usr/share/doc/fIcy/NEWS.rst
  /usr/share/doc/fIcy/README.rst
  /usr/share/doc/fIcy/TODO.rst

